# Moonlander – Ubuntu Installation Guide

This guide describes how to set up the Moonlander project on a fresh Ubuntu system.

---

## 1. Update System

Open a terminal and run:

sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y

---

## 2. Install Basic Development Tools

Install essential build tools and utilities:

sudo apt install -y build-essential git cmake ninja-build

---

## 3. Install Qt6 (via Qt Online Installer)

### Download Installer

1. Go to: https://doc.qt.io/qt-6  
2. Click "Download Qt" (top right corner)  
3. Choose Community Edition  
4. Download Qt Online Installer for Linux x64  

---

### Run Installer

Open terminal and navigate to your Downloads folder:

cd ~/Downloads

Make the installer executable:

chmod +x qt-unified-linux-x64-*.run

Run the installer:

./qt-unified-linux-x64-*.run

---

### Fix Common Installer Error (XCB)

If you see:
"The required xcb cursor platform library was not found"

Install missing dependencies:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y \
libxcb-cursor0 \
libxcb-xinerama0 \
libxkbcommon-x11-0 \
libxcb-render0 \
libxcb-shape0 \
libxcb-xfixes0 \
libxcb-randr0 \
libxcb-image0 \
libxcb-keysyms1 \
libxcb-icccm4 \
libxcb-sync1 \
libxcb-xkb1 \
libx11-xcb1 \
libgl1-mesa-dev

Then rerun the installer.

---

### Qt Installation Settings

In the Qt Installer:

- Log in with your Qt account (create one if needed)
- Choose Custom Installation
- Select:
  - Latest Qt Version (e.g. Qt 6.10+)
  - Desktop gcc 64-bit
  - Qt Creator
  - Build Tools:
    - CMake
    - Ninja
    - Qt Installer Framework

---

## 4. Install NLopt

sudo apt install -y libnlopt-dev

---

## 5. Install nlohmann JSON

sudo apt install -y nlohmann-json3-dev

---

## 6. Clone Repository

### Fork Repository

1. Go to your repository on GitHub  
2. Click Fork  
3. This creates your own copy of the project  

---

### Clone Your Fork

mkdir -p ~/Code
cd ~/Code
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/moonlander.git
cd moonlander

---

## 7. Build the Project in Qt Creator

Start Qt Creator:

~/Qt/Tools/QtCreator/bin/qtcreator

Then:

1. File → Open File or Project  
2. Select:
   moonlander/CMakeLists.txt  

3. Choose Kit:
   Desktop Qt 6 (gcc 64-bit)

4. IMPORTANT: Check the Kit configuration
   - Compiler should be GCC (/usr/bin/g++)
   - Qt version should match installed Qt (e.g. 6.10)
   - CMake should be detected

5. If configuration fails:
   - Delete the build folder manually:
     rm -rf build
   - Reopen the project in Qt Creator
   - Reconfigure

6. Configure Project

7. Build the project:
   Build → Build Project (Ctrl + B)

8. Run the application:
   Run → Run

---

## Notes

- Ubuntu uses system packages → no vcpkg required
- Qt is installed via Qt Online Installer for latest version
- GCC is used as the default compiler
- This setup is significantly simpler than Windows

---

## Troubleshooting

### Compiler missing

sudo apt install -y build-essential

---

### Git not installed

sudo apt install -y git

---

### NLopt not found

sudo apt install -y libnlopt-dev

---

### JSON not found

sudo apt install -y nlohmann-json3-dev

---

## Recommended Platform

- Ubuntu 24.04 LTS (preferred)
- Ubuntu 22.04 (works, but not primary target)

---

✅ After completing these steps, the Moonlander project should build and run successfully on Ubuntu.
